                <note rend="inline" type="source">861a.01/67: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Harbin</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Jenkins</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Harbin</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-08-31T18:00:00+08:26">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 31, 1921—6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received August 31—4:29 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Petroff, Chairman Council of Ministers Far Eastern Republic, and Kraajew Nikoff
                        [<hi rend="italic">Kozhevnikov</hi>], Assistant Secretary of State, arrived
                    in Harbin yesterday from Chita <hi rend="italic">en route</hi> to Dairen where
                    they expect to confer with Japanese. Party had some difficulty with maritime
                    customs but matter finally arranged and they expect continue journey today.
                    Legation informed.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Jenkins</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
